      • parseLiteralLength

        public static final int parseLiteralLength(CharSequence s,
                                           int start,
                                           int stop,
                                           String errmsg)
        Determine the length of a literal value.

        This static method may be used to determine the length of a literal value. The ``start'' parameter indicates the starting index into the text and ``stop'' indicates the stop index.

        This method will stop when the first structural character is found or when ``stop'' is reached, whichever comes first. Note, because it is static no limits are enforced as is with parse.

        Parameters:
        s - text to be parsed
        start - start position in text
        stop - stop position in text
        errmsg - error message for thrown SyntaxException
        Returns:
        the length of the literal value

      • parseLiteral

        public static final <V> V parseLiteral(CharSequence s,
                                       int start,
                                       int length,
                                       ValueFactory<V,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?> factory)
        Parse a single literal value.

        This static method may be used to parse a single literal:

        • boolean (true or false)
        • null
        • number
        • string
        No limits are enforced (as is with parse) because this method is static.

        Note, the third argument is a length not a position. It indicates the number of characters to be parsed.

        Parameters:
        s - text to be parsed
        start - start position in text
        length - number of characters to parse
        Returns:
        an object for the parsed literal
